<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1371,1506]" pageId="24" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1444,1470]" pageId="24" pageNumber="156">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was recently described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Smetana, A." box="[760,1063,1443,1470]" pageId="24" pageNumber="156" pagination="591 - 599" refId="ref19722" refString="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Smetana, A. (2016) New species and records of the genus Geodromicus Redtenbacher, 1857 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae) from Taiwan. Zootaxa, 4066 (5), 591 - 599. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4066.5.7" type="journal article" year="2016">Shavrin &amp; Smetana (2016)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1132,1290,1443,1470]" country="Taiwan" name="Nantou" pageId="24" pageNumber="156">Nantou Hsien</collectingRegion>
, Central 
<collectingCountry name="Taiwan" pageId="24" pageNumber="156">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. The distribution of the species as in 
<figureCitation box="[617,712,1479,1506]" captionStart="FIGURE 113" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 113. Distribution of 21 species of Geodromicus in China: 1–G. abdominalis, 2–G. amplissimus, 3–G. aokii, 4–G. beibienkoi, 5–G. chinensis, 6–G. cupreostigma, 7–G. formosanus, 8–G. frigidus, 9–G. hammondi, 10–G. lestevoides, 11–G. magnus sp. n., 12–G. namucuoicus sp. n., 13–G. ohkurai, 14–G. philydroides, 15–G. shii sp. n., 16–G. sibiricus, 17–G. sinuatocollis, 18–G. sinuatus, 19–G. smetanai, 20–G. subquadratus sp. n., 21–G. taiwanensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884852/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="156">Fig. 113</figureCitation>
. It is recorded here from 
<collectingRegion box="[994,1155,1479,1505]" country="Taiwan" name="Hualien" pageId="24" pageNumber="156">Hualien Hsien</collectingRegion>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
